path.desc: Discovered on April 13th, Thomas Jefferson's birthday, the system was named in honor of Thomas Jefferson by Captain Christopher Holt.

path.desc:
Named for Jacob Holst IV, the super-wealthy patron who financed the colony expedition. Holst was heavily contested during the First Contact War. The entire area of prime space has been rendered unstable and hyperspace navigation is extremely hazardous due to the use of Triangulum mines during the war.
As a result Holst has been largely cut off. It is still nominally part of the USA, but contact has been sporadic and limited since the First Contact War.
path.title: Holst

path.title: Sol System

path.desc:
Originally named Grant's Star, the system was named by Commodore Grant Sharpe ostensibly after President U.S. Grant, but also after himself as a tongue-in-cheek taunt to Captain Christopher Holt.
During the First Contact war this system served as a rally point and fall-back point for United System's fleets. To facilitate this role a make-shift refueling station was built here and named Grant Station.
This initial station was destroyed by Valandaux forces during the battle of Grant Station.
The current Grant Station was rebuilt after the war with the primary role of a listening post to watch the Valandaux Neutral Zone.
path.title: Grant Station

path.desc: This system is rumored to exist based on pre-war explorations, as well as military reports during the war. However, its existence was never officially confirmed. Some rumors hold that this system was actually the place were first contact was actually made with Valandaux ships.

path.desc:
Barnard's star is a red dwarf initially dinstinguished by it's near proximity to the Sol System.
Barnard's star is host to one rocky planet about of about 3 earth masses. The system is deemed uninhabitable and has not been the target of any colonization efforts. Never the less, the system has taken on vital strategic significance. It is a crossroads of several important hyperlanes, and serves as the single system that connects the Earth Gov. Territories on either side.
Resources: Defensive Installations Communications Array
